{"item_id": "case:vllm@4685a630a293", "kind": "case", "repo": "vllm", "findings": [{"severity": "suggestion", "category": "memory/allocation-overhead", "claim": "In vllm/model_executor/models/minicpm.py, MiniCPMMoE.forward switches fused_experts from inplace=True to inplace=False. With inplace=False, fused_moe.py (line 1723) allocates a fresh output tensor via torch.empty_like(hidden_states) each MoE forward instead of writing into hidden_states in-place, adding one extra [num_tokens, hidden_size] activation allocation per MoE layer per forward step. This is on the per-step hot path (MiniCPMMoE.forward is called by MiniCPMDecoderLayer.forward for every MoE layer every decode/prefill step when the model has num_experts>0). However, this change is effectively forced for correctness: utils.disable_inplace() returns True for torch>=2.9 (torch custom ops can't alias inputs, issue #26378), and fused_experts asserts `not inplace or not disable_inplace()`, so inplace=True would crash on torch>=2.9. Thus the extra allocation is unavoidable on modern torch and only marginally increases activation memory/allocator traffic on the pre-2.9 path. Net regression is minor and secondary to correctness.", "confidence": 0.55, "hot_path": true, "default_enabled": true, "leaf": "extra-tensor-allocation-on-hot-path", "file": "vllm/model_executor/models/minicpm.py"}], "leak_attempt": false, "latency_s": 22.35, "n_turns": 1, "cost": 0.4283495, "gate": false, "decomposed": false, "n_groups": 1, "scenario": null, "tokens": {"in": 0, "out": 0}}
