{"item_id": "case:Megatron-LM@f54403492e3c", "kind": "case", "repo": "Megatron-LM", "findings": [{"severity": "important", "category": "host_side_overhead/jit_compilation", "claim": "CheckpointWithoutOutput's activation-restore path now calls _get_share_storage(), which on first invocation triggers torch.utils.cpp_extension.load_inline to JIT-compile a C++ extension at RUNTIME. This is called from the backward/recompute-restore path of CheckpointWithoutOutput, which is used in default selective-recompute paths (transformer_layer input_layernorm_checkpoint / pre_mlp_norm_checkpoint, TEGroupedMLP moe_act activation_recompute, MLA qkv_up_checkpoint) whenever recompute_granularity='selective'. The old code did a plain resize_+copy_ with zero build dependency. load_inline invokes a full C++ compile (nvcc/g++), can take tens of seconds to minutes on first backward, requires a compiler + torch dev headers present in the runtime environment, and writes to a shared TORCH_EXTENSIONS_DIR — with many ranks compiling concurrently this can serialize/contend and stall the whole first training step. If the toolchain is missing, training crashes at first backward instead of a config-time error.", "confidence": 0.82, "file": "megatron/core/tensor_parallel/random.py", "hot_path": false, "leaf": "runtime_jit_compilation_stall", "default_enabled": true}], "leak_attempt": false, "latency_s": 20.86, "n_turns": 1, "cost": 0.4736825, "gate": false, "decomposed": false, "n_groups": 1, "scenario": null, "tokens": {"in": 0, "out": 0}}
