{"item_id": "case:vllm@ffc0a2798b11", "kind": "case", "repo": "vllm", "findings": [{"severity": "important", "category": "numerical-correctness-vs-perf-tradeoff", "claim": "Restores DeepEP LL dispatch quantization consistency: when running on SM100/Blackwell with DeepGemm E8M0 enabled (BatchedDeepGemmExperts.supports_packed_ue8m0_act_scales() returns True by default), post_init_setup sets self.use_ue8m0_dispatch=True, but the parent snapshot's low_latency_dispatch() call never forwarded round_scale/use_ue8m0. Thus the dispatch kernel produced plain fp8 scales while the downstream DeepGemm masked-gemm expected packed ue8m0 scales — a scale-format mismatch. This fix passes round_scale=self.use_ue8m0_dispatch and use_ue8m0=self.use_ue8m0_dispatch so dispatch emits the correct ue8m0-rounded scales matching the gemm path. This is on the per-forward MoE dispatch hot path (prepare_async -> buffer.low_latency_dispatch called every MoE layer per step). Being a correctness/consistency fix rather than a slowdown, it is not itself a perf regression; but the surrounding path is default-enabled on SM100 + DeepGemm E8M0 (no opt-in env flag needed beyond fp8 dispatch).", "confidence": 0.55, "file": "vllm/model_executor/layers/fused_moe/deepep_ll_prepare_finalize.py", "hot_path": true, "default_enabled": true, "leaf": null}], "leak_attempt": false, "latency_s": 19.49, "n_turns": 1, "cost": 0.2209985, "gate": false, "decomposed": false, "n_groups": 1, "scenario": null, "tokens": {"in": 0, "out": 0}}
{"item_id": "pair:DeepSpeed@f897b6739482->15ad92b459c6", "kind": "pair", "repo": "DeepSpeed", "findings": [{"severity": "suggestion", "category": "gpu-sync/stream-serialization", "claim": "The fix in reduce_independent_p_g_buckets_and_remove_grads adds a bidirectional stream sync (reduction_stream.wait_stream(current) + current.wait_stream(reduction_stream)) before swapping the double ipg_buffer index. This runs on the gradient-reduction path once per full ipg bucket (i.e. once per bucket boundary during backward, on the hot path per microbatch), and is enabled by default when contiguous_gradients and overlap_comm are both True. The bidirectional wait_stream forces the compute stream to wait on the reduction stream, which can partially serialize the comm/compute overlap that overlap_comm is intended to provide, reducing GPU utilization slightly. However this is a correctness fix (loss going to 0 with double-buffer swap in ZeRO-2) and wait_stream only inserts CUDA events (no host sync), so the cost is small and only triggers at bucket-swap boundaries, not per-parameter. Non-CUDA/synchronized accelerators skip it via resolves_data_dependency(). Net: minor, justified overhead to fix a real correctness bug, not a genuine regression.", "confidence": 0.55, "file": "deepspeed/runtime/zero/stage_1_and_2.py", "hot_path": true, "leaf": "unnecessary-gpu-synchronization", "default_enabled": false}], "leak_attempt": false, "latency_s": 22.24, "n_turns": 1, "cost": 0.3390835, "gate": false, "decomposed": false, "n_groups": 1, "scenario": null, "tokens": {"in": 0, "out": 0}}
