{"item_id": "case:Megatron-LM@485ed1817d18", "kind": "case", "repo": "Megatron-LM", "findings": [{"severity": "important", "category": "redundant-collective-communication", "claim": "In `_communicate_shapes` of BridgeCommunicator, the shape tensor was broadcast twice consecutively on `src_grid_broadcast_pg` (a duplicate `dist.broadcast` call). This commit removes the redundant second broadcast. Before this fix, every shape-communication on the source-grid broadcast path issued two identical NCCL broadcasts, doubling the collective count for shape sync. Shape communication happens on the send-forward / recv-backward P2P path per pipeline microbatch exchange between grids, so the redundant broadcast added a needless synchronous NCCL collective on the inter-module bridge hot path in the default configuration. This commit is the FIX (removes the regression), not the introduction.", "confidence": 0.78, "file": "megatron/core/pipeline_parallel/bridge_communicator.py", "hot_path": true, "default_enabled": true, "leaf": "redundant-collective-communication"}], "leak_attempt": false, "latency_s": 18.48, "n_turns": 3, "cost": 0.2519915, "gate": false, "decomposed": true, "n_groups": 3, "scenario": null, "tokens": {"in": 0, "out": 0}}
